summary:
The Security Council, recalling previous resolutions on Liberia and West Africa, 
applauds Liberia's cooperation with the Kimberley Process Certification Scheme and notes progress towards meeting its requirements. 
The Council welcomes Liberia's proposed Certificate of Origin regime and the interim report of the UN Panel of Experts. 
Having reviewed measures imposed by resolution 1521 (2003), the Council concludes sufficient progress has been made. 
Determining the situation in Liberia remains a threat to international peace and security, 
the Council:
1. Terminates diamond measures imposed by paragraph 6 of resolution 1521 (2003);
2. Encourages the Kimberley Process to report in 90 days on Liberia's application;
3. Decides to review termination after considering the UN Panel of Experts' final report and Kimberley Process report, focusing on Liberia's compliance;
4. Remains actively seized of the matter.
